The warranty and training offerings mentioned in the IKO-Lumina agreement include:

1. **Warranty**:
   - **Product Warranty**: 20 to 25 years, depending on the system size and whether the installation is done by an REC Certified Solar Professional.
   - **Power Warranty**: 25 years across all system sizes, ensuring power output is maintained at 98% in year one, with a degradation rate of 0.25% annually. By year 25, the power output is guaranteed to be 92%.
   - **Labor Warranty**: For systems installed by an REC Certified Solar Professional, the labor warranty is either 10 or 25 years, depending on the system size.

2. **Training**:
   - No explicit details regarding formal training offerings are provided in the text, but the warranty benefits are clearly tied to the involvement of an REC Certified Solar Professional, suggesting that installers must undergo a certification process to qualify for extended warranties. 

For more detailed information on specific warranty conditions or any additional training requirements, you would need to consult the relevant sections on www.recgroup.com, as referenced in the document【5†source】.

GENERAL DATA

Cell type:
80 half-cut REC bifacial, heterojunction cells with  

lead-free, gapless technology

Glass: 0.13 in (3.2 mm) solar glass with anti-reflective surface treatment 
in accordance with EN 12150

Backsheet: Highly resistant polymer (black)

Frame: Anodized aluminum (black)

Junction box:
4-part, 4 bypass diodes, lead-free 

 IP68 rated, in accordance with IEC 62790 

Connectors: Stäubli MC4 PV-KBT4/KST4 (12 AWG) 
in accordance with IEC 62852, IP68 only when connected

Cable: 12 AWG (4 mm²) PV wire, 67 + 67 in (1.7 + 1.7 m) 
in accordance with EN 50618

Dimensions: 68.1 x 44.0 x 1.2 in (20.77 c2) / 1730 x 1118 x 30 mm (1.93 m2)

Weight: 47.4 lbs (21.5 kg)

Origin: Made in Singapore

Typical low irradiance performance of module at STC:

Panels per pallet: 33

# 【13†IKO-Lumina agreement - June 7, 2023 - final and executed, with schedules (1).pdf†file-XKLsnDP5GFb5lR2ljUiotUR0】
Measurements in inches [mm]

GENERAL DATA

Cell type:
80 half-cut REC bifacial, heterojunction cells with  

lead-free, gapless technology

Glass: 0.13 in (3.2 mm) solar glass with anti-reflective surface treatment 
in accordance with EN 12150

Backsheet: Highly resistant polymer (black)

Frame: Anodized aluminum (black)

Junction box:
4-part, 4 bypass diodes, lead-free 

 IP68 rated, in accordance with IEC 62790 

Connectors: Stäubli MC4 PV-KBT4/KST4 (12 AWG) 
in accordance with IEC 62852, IP68 only when connected

Cable: 12 AWG (4 mm²) PV wire, 67 + 67 in (1.7 + 1.7 m) 
in accordance with EN 50618

Dimensions: 68.1 x 44.0 x 1.2 in (20.77 c2) / 1730 x 1118 x 30 mm (1.93 m2)

Weight: 47.4 lbs (21.5 kg)

Origin: Made in Singapore

Typical low irradiance performance of module at STC:

DELIVERY INFORMATION

Panels per pallet: 33

Panels per 40 c GP/high cube container: 858 (26 pallets)

Panels per 53 c truck: 858 (26 pallets)

WARRANTY

Standard REC ProTrust

Installed by an REC 
Certified Solar Professional No Yes Yes

System Size All ≤25 kW 25-500 kW

Product Warranty (yrs) 20 25 25

Power Warranty (yrs) 25 25 25

Labor Warranty (yrs) 0 25 10

Power in Year 1 98% 98% 98%

Annual Degradation 0.25% 0.25% 0.25%

Power in Year 25 92% 92% 92%
The REC ProTrust Warranty is only available on panels purchased 
through an REC Certified Solar Professional installer. Warranty 

conditions apply. See www.recgroup.com for more details.

TEMPERATURE RATINGS*

Nominal Module Operating Temperature: 44°C (±2°C)

Temperature coefficient of PMAX: -0.24 %/°C

Temperature coefficient of VOC: -0.24 %/°C

Temperature coefficient of ISC: 0.04 %/°C
*The temperature coefficients stated are linear values

MAXIMUM RATINGS

Operational temperature: -40 ... +85°C

System voltage: 1000 V

Test load (front):  + 7000 Pa (146 lbs/c2)*

Test load (rear): - 4000 Pa (83.5 lbs/c2)*

Series fuse rating: 25 A

Reverse current: 25 A
* See installation manual for mounting instructions. 

Design load = Test load / 1.5 (safety factor)
